<StoryPage
  title="About — Time Series of India"
  description="Why Time Series of India exists: turning India's official public data — raw Excel releases and reports — into clear, insightful charts and explainers."
>
  <SectionHeader label="About" />
  <article class="prose">
    <h3>What this is</h3>
    <p>
      India publishes some of the world's richest public data, but most of it lives inside Excel
      attachments and ministry portals, filed the way departments work, not the way questions are
      asked. Time Series of India does the translation once, in public:
      official releases become clear charts and short explainers — swipeable beats, written
      reads, interactive dashboards — every number traceable to the release it came from.
    </p>

    <h3>One theme at a time</h3>
    <p>
      The economy section — how India moves money, from RBI and NPCI statistics — is the first
      theme. The same method works on any India-specific public dataset:
      environment, infrastructure, demographics, governance. New themes will land as good
      datasources are found and explored. If you know a public dataset that deserves this treatment,
      <a href="https://github.com/time-series-of-india/tsoi/issues">suggest it on GitHub</a> —
      finding them is half the fun of this project.
    </p>
    <p>
      The code behind the site — parsers, pipeline, charts — is
      <a href="https://github.com/time-series-of-india/tsoi">open source</a>.
    </p>


    <h3>Sources, reuse &amp; disclaimer</h3>
    <p>
      Every figure derives from a publicly released official dataset, and each read and dashboard
      names its source — see <a href="/data">the data page</a> for the full list per theme. Data
      is © its publishing agency (currently the Reserve Bank of India and NPCI) and reproduced
      with acknowledgement; where our figures and a source disagree, the source is correct. Map
      boundaries are illustrative only and are not an authority on any boundary — refer to the
      Survey of India. You're welcome to cite TSOI's charts and writing with attribution and a
      link; for reuse of the underlying statistics beyond informational, non-commercial purposes,
      check the source agency's own terms.
    </p>
    <p>
      Time Series of India is provided for informational and educational purposes only. It is
      independent and <strong>not affiliated with, endorsed by, or representing</strong> the
      Reserve Bank of India, the National Payments Corporation of India, or the Government of
      India. Figures may differ from the primary source; verify against the original before
      relying on them. The site is provided “as is,” without warranties of any kind, and its
      maintainers accept no liability for decisions made on the basis of it. Trademarks (UPI,
      IMPS, RuPay, and bank or app names) belong to their respective owners and are used only to
      identify the services they name.
    </p>
  </article>
</StoryPage>

